# App Config

Backend-driven navigation and feature flag system. The entire navigation structure is fetched from `/v4/profile-config` on login and drives the app's UI.

## Core components

```
lib/core/app_config/
  domain/
    app_config.dart         # AppConfig — immutable config (settings + navigation)
    global_settings.dart    # GlobalSettings — feature flags
    nav_item.dart           # NavItem — a single navigation destination
    nav_type.dart           # NavType enum — route | webpage | custom
  navigation/
    app_navigator.dart      # AppNavigator — executes navigation based on NavType
  adapters/
    app_config_adapter.dart # Parses API response into AppConfig
  app_config_controller.dart # Controller + appConfig atom
  app_config_service.dart    # Service — fetches config from API
```

## AppConfig

Immutable configuration fetched once on login. Never mutated after construction.

```dart
class AppConfig {
  final GlobalSettings settings;      // Feature flags
  final List<NavItem> navigation;     // Top-level nav items (tabs, menu)
  
  NavItem get firstPage => navigation.first;
  NavItem? findByRoute(String route) { ... }
}
```

## GlobalSettings

Feature flags returned by the backend. Controls which infrastructure services are active.

```dart
class GlobalSettings {
  final bool enablePushNotifications;
  final bool enableIntercom;
  final bool enableLocationTracking;
  final bool enableNotificationsCentre;
}
```

## NavItem

A single navigation destination. Can represent a bottom nav tab, menu link, or nested sub-link.

```dart
class NavItem {
  final String route;                 // Route path or URL
  final String label;                 // Display label
  final String? icon;                 // Icon key (resolved by AppIcons.resolve)
  final String? description;          // Optional description
  final NavType type;                 // How this item navigates
  final Map<String, dynamic> config;  // Raw config passed to destination
  final List<NavItem> links;          // Nested links (for menus)
  
  Future<void> navigate(BuildContext context, {bool forRoot = true});
}
```

## NavType

```dart
enum NavType {
  route,    // Standard GoRouter push — route string is the path
  webpage,  // Opens URL in AppWebView
  custom,   // Handled by injected handler (e.g. Intercom, camera)
}
```

## AppNavigator

Central navigation executor. Never call GoRouter directly from a NavItem — always use `item.navigate(context)` or `AppNavigator.navigate(context, item)`.

### Custom handlers

Custom handlers are injected from outside `core/` to keep the module decoupled from app-specific logic.

```dart
// In AuthBuilder after Authenticated:
AppNavigator.registerCustomHandler(
  'intercom',
  (context, item) async => IntercomHandler().openMessenger(),
);

AppNavigator.registerCustomHandler(
  'kiosk',
  (context, item) async => context.push('/kiosk', extra: item.config),
);
```

On logout, call `appConfigController.onLogout()` to clear handlers.

## appConfig atom

Global `AsyncAtom<AppConfig>` — self-registers for `resetAllAtoms()` on logout.

```dart
final appConfig = AsyncAtom<AppConfig>();

// States:
Idle()     // before login
Loading()  // fetch in progress
Success()  // config ready, navigation active
Failure()  // fetch failed — show error + retry
```

## Wiring

### 1. AuthBuilder

```dart
case Authenticated():
  await appConfigController.load();
  
  // Register custom handlers
  AppNavigator.registerCustomHandler('intercom', ...);
  AppNavigator.registerCustomHandler('kiosk', ...);

case Unauthenticated():
  appConfigController.onLogout(); // clears nav handlers
  resetAllAtoms();                // resets appConfig atom
```

### 2. Router redirect

```dart
redirect: (context, state) {
  final auth   = authState.value;
  final config = appConfig.value;
  
  if (auth is Unauthenticated) return '/login';
  if (auth is Authenticated) {
    if (config is Loading || config is Idle) return '/loader';
    if (config is Failure)                   return '/config-error';
    if (config is Success) return null; // navigation ready
  }
  return null;
}
```

### 3. Bottom nav / AppShell

Render navigation from `config.navigation`:

```dart
appConfig(
  loading: () => const AppLoaderScreen(),
  failure: (msg) => ConfigErrorScreen(onRetry: appConfigController.reload),
  success: (config) => AppShell(navItems: config.navigation),
)
```

### 4. Bottom navigation bar

```dart
BottomNavigationBar(
  items: navItems.map((item) => BottomNavigationBarItem(
    icon: Icon(AppIcons.resolve(item.icon)),
    label: item.label,
  )).toList(),
  onTap: (index) => navItems[index].navigate(context, forRoot: false),
)
```

### 5. Menu screen

Render links from a NavItem:

```dart
final menuItem = appConfigController.current?.findByRoute('app-menu');

ListView(
  children: menuItem?.links.map((link) => ListTile(
    title: Text(link.label),
    subtitle: link.description != null ? Text(link.description!) : null,
    leading: Icon(AppIcons.resolve(link.icon)),
    onTap: () => link.navigate(context),
  )).toList() ?? [],
)
```

## AppIcons

Icon resolver in `lib/core/ui/icons/app_icons.dart`. Maps string icon keys to Lucide IconData.

```dart
AppIcons.resolve('home')      // LucideIcons.home
AppIcons.resolve('rewards')   // LucideIcons.gift
AppIcons.resolve('profile')   // LucideIcons.user
AppIcons.resolve(null)        // LucideIcons.circle (fallback)
```

To add a new icon, add it to the switch statement in `AppIcons.resolve()`.

## WebView route

The `/webview` route must be defined in `router.dart`:

```dart
GoRoute(
  path: '/webview',
  builder: (context, state) {
    final args = state.extra as NavArgs;
    final url = args.config['url'] as String;
    final title = args.config['title'] as String?;
    return AppWebView(url: url, title: title);
  },
)
```

`AppWebView` is a reusable widget in `lib/core/ui/webview/app_webview.dart`.

## Rules

- **Never hardcode bottom nav items** — always render from `config.navigation`
- **Never call GoRouter directly from a NavItem** — use `item.navigate(context)`
- **Custom handlers must be registered in AuthBuilder** after `Authenticated`
- **Config is immutable** — never mutate after construction
- **Always use `appConfigController.current`** for null-safe access to the current config
- **WebView route must exist** at `/webview` in `router.dart`
- **Icon keys are resolved by `AppIcons.resolve()`** — never hardcode IconData in navigation
- **On logout, call `appConfigController.onLogout()`** before `resetAllAtoms()`
- **NavArgs is passed via GoRouter's `extra`** — destination screens read it from `state.extra`
- **`forRoot` parameter controls navigation shell** — pass `false` when navigating between tabs

## Adding a new custom handler

1. Register the handler in `AuthBuilder` after `Authenticated`:
   ```dart
   AppNavigator.registerCustomHandler('my-custom-route', (context, item) async {
     // Handle navigation
   });
   ```

2. Backend sends a NavItem with `type: "custom"` and `route: "my-custom-route"`

3. When tapped, `AppNavigator` calls your registered handler

## Error handling

If config fetch fails:
- Router redirects to `/config-error`
- Show error message + retry button
- Retry calls `appConfigController.reload()`

## Null-safe access

```dart
final config = appConfigController.current; // AppConfig? or null
if (config != null) {
  final firstPage = config.firstPage;
  final menuItem = config.findByRoute('app-menu');
}
```
